{"source_key":"sha256-364390994d45a450aa62c8b6d3ca2577","record_index":1224,"record_hash":"sha256:5c947b9d82ca527fd0e5c58040d9f266062c0ec56bb335dc208c8d12932efbc1","timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:19:05.202Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"**Findings**\\n\\n- [P1] [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:374](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:374) `get_session_timeline(..., max_turns)` advertises a bounded “small window” API, but still reads and indexes the entire `:transcript` list before applying the turn window. For long sessions this can hydrate tons of data just to return one turn. Slice turns first, then fetch only referenced record hashes.\\n\\n- [P1] [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:112](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:112) `TimelineTurn.records: Vec<Value>` leaks the stored transcript record shape as public API: `record_hash`, `record_index`, `source_key`, `source_record`, provider-ish raw fields, etc. That’s too early for a crate-level export. Use a typed public record DTO, or keep this function private/internal until the consumer contract is real.\\n\\n- [P2] [crates/but-agentlog/src/lib.rs:12](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/lib.rs:12) Re-exporting `SessionTimeline`, `TimelineTurn`, and `get_session_timeline` makes this shape the crate boundary immediately. I’d avoid the re-export for now unless there’s already an external caller that needs exactly this. The current shape reads like a storage reader, not a stable domain/API surface.\\n\\n- [P2] [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:117](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:117) Public fields like `capture_kind: String` and `environment_snapshot_status: String` mirror serialized storage instead of domain enums. That weakens the boundary and makes invalid states public